  "page_number": 5,
  "context": "5 a rank of “Lecturer”, “Senior Lecturer”, or “Professorial Lecturer” (UP Faculty Manual).\n\nSection 3 A lecturer is a faculty member who has earned units and is currently pursuing MA/MS degree program aligned/allied to his/her field of specialization. A senior lecturer is a full-fledged MA/MS degree holder aligned/allied to his/her field of specialization whose performance and accomplishments are comparable to at least an Assistant Professor I rank. A professional lecturer is a full-fledged PhD/EdD or other doctorate degree holder whose performance and accomplishments.\n\nV. General Policies\n\nSection 1 All faculty members holding permanent positions/items must first be given regular WL for the semester before additional teachers (under Contract of Service) will be hired. Section 2 Faculty members must be informed of their tentative teaching loads (TL) at least one (1) week before the start of classes. Section 3 The percentage distribution of job function vis-à-vis major thrusts of the University shall be specified in the Individual Performance Commitment and Review (IPCR). Section 4 A faculty member with a WL & TL in excess of 30 hours/week within office hours, after office hours on a scheduled workday, on a rest day or scheduled day off, holiday, or special non-working day shall be entitled to an honorarium/overtime pay for the teaching overload subject to the availability of funds or is granted service credit equivalence. Section 5 All other assignments with monetary remuneration shall not be given any workload equivalent. Section 6 The IGP Manual of the University shall be used as guide when a faculty member is involved in Production function. Section 7 A faculty member must satisfy the mandatory functions before accepting optional loads. Section 8 In the exigency of the service, additional loads may be given to faculty with more than the minimum WL.",
  "qa_pairs": [
    {
      "question": "What is the minimum WL a faculty member must have to be eligible for additional loads?",
      "answer": "The minimum WL for a faculty member to be eligible for additional loads is 30 hours/week within office hours, after office hours on a scheduled workday, on a rest day or scheduled day off, holiday, or special non-working day."
    },
    {
      "question": "What is the criteria for determining a faculty member's rank?",
      "answer": "A faculty member's rank is determined by their units earned and degree program aligned/allied to their field of specialization. A senior lecturer is a full-fledged MA/MS degree holder aligned/allied to their field of specialization whose performance and accomplishments are comparable to at least an Assistant Professor I rank."
    },
    {
      "question": "What is the purpose of the Individual Performance Commitment and Review (IPCR)?",
      "answer": "The IPCR manual of the University shall be used as a guide when a faculty member is involved in Production function. The IPCR is used to specify the percentage distribution of job functions vis-à-vis major thrusts of the University."
    },
    {
      "question": "What happens if a faculty member has a WL & TL in excess of 30 hours/week within office hours, after office hours on a scheduled workday, on a rest day or scheduled day off, holiday, or special non-working day?",
      "answer": "The faculty member is entitled to an honorarium/overtime pay for the teaching overload subject to the availability of funds or is granted service credit equivalence."
    },
    {
      "question": "What is the policy on additional loads in case of exigency of the service?",
      "answer": "In the exigency of the service, additional loads may be given to faculty with more than the minimum WL."
